      "part_type": "Hadith",
      "path": "/books/al-kafi:5:2:159:12",
      "text": [
        " سَمِعْتُهُ يَقُولُ حِيلَةُ الرَّجُلِ فِي بَابِ مَكْسَبِهِ ."
      ],
      "translations": {
        "en.hubeali": [
          "Al Husayn Bin Muhammad, from Moalla Bin Muhammad, from Al Washa, ",
          "(It has been narrated) from Abu Al-Hassan<sup>asws</sup>, said, ‘I heard him<sup>asws</sup> saying: ‘The skilfulness of a man is a door (way) to his earnings (for living)’."
        ],
        "en.sarwar": [
          "12. Al-Husayn from Muhammad has narrated from Mu’alla’ ibn Muhammad from af-Washsha’ who has said the foiiowing: “I once heard him (the Imam), ‘Alayhi al-Salam, saying, ‘The skillfulness of a man is for his earning a living.’” "
        ]
      }
